 EMOTICON END-->  <p>____________________________________________________________

Some say the world will end in fire;
Some say in ice.
From what I've tasted of desire
I hold with those who favor fire.
But if it had to perish twice,
I think I know enough of hate
To know that for destruction ice
Is also great
And would suffice.
____________________________________________________________</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 10:02 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hehehehe...</span><hr size=1> First of all, I can't get over that fro in the picture.  ROTFLMAO.  Sorry, just side tracked there.<br>
<br>
<br>
Since stuns are one of our major uses in upper exp groups, I would LOVE to see a more effective stun or a large scale stun.  I suppose the gaters are there for the great challanges that they present.  However, having that specialized stun would definitely make us a desired for those special circumstances.  I don't know if saying &quot;no more gaters&quot; would be a good thing.  In moderation it would be wonderful.  The resist percentage would probably be a factor if they tried it.<br>
<br>
W.F.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 10:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lure stun, that interrupts giant type mobs</span><hr size=1> I like this idea a lot.  Even if it was just an interrupt stun, as a 2 second stun might be too powerful with enough wizards against top level encounters.  It doesn't dilute any &quot;class defining abilities&quot; from other classes, it doesn't help us solo, and it doesn't increase our damage output.  It does make wizards very valuable in certain situations, and give them a unique talent that would make them more desirable in situations ranging from top level encounters to some of the tougher experience camps (chardok comes to mind).<br>
<br>
Note that mobs which currently resist magic based lures would also resist this spell, so there are still opportunities for challenges and surprises not addressed by the lure stun.<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra (Arcis)<br>
58 wizard of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unicolheartsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicol Heartsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 11:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lure stun, that interrupts giant type mobs</span><hr size=1> These mobs don't resist stuns.  They just aren't effected.<br>
Making a way to stun them or stop them from casting would be some sort of silence or counterspell.  <br>
<br>
The name &quot;lure stun&quot; is misleading, and pretty much off target.  However, if we get a stun that works on normally unstunable mobs, it would probably be like the proc on the tranquil staff.  (Yeah, monks can do it but we can't.)<br>
<br>
This proc causes insane amounts of hate.  I have no idea whether it can currently stop a gate or CH from a stormgiant.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 12:37 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yes...</span><hr size=1> Most of the mobs that can't get stunned will still take the damage.  Just won't be stunned.  Took me a few kills to figured it out.  I was an idiot...  Well... STILL AM!!!!<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvulpdiscoinferno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vulp DiscoInferno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 1:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes...</span><hr size=1> Tstaff proc doesn't stun unstunnable mobs (least thats what my monk friends tell me) Yeah lure stun is a little misleading, but us having a stun that would interupt giant type mobs would make use very desireable, not increase solo ability mana regen or damage output (verants stupid objections) <p>____________________________________________________________

Some say the world will end in fire;
Some say in ice.
From what I've tasted of desire
I hold with those who favor fire.
But if it had to perish twice,
I think I know enough of hate
To know that for destruction ice
Is also great
And would suffice.
____________________________________________________________</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1159<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/01 12:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes...</span><hr size=1> I think you can still interrupt casting with the stun even if they are immune to stunning, but I haven't been able to confirm nor deny this yet in actual testing.  Probably not but its an interesting thought at least.<br>
<br>
I think Wizards should get a spell at lower level that does no damage, casts fairly quickly, and all it does is interrupt the target's casting unless he resists it.  This would allow us to be the supreme class at stopping casters, fit our concept pretty well, and be damn handy.<br>
<br>
Oh, and screw PVP if it causes problems there, this is about the game as a whole not a splinter bunch of servers, balance it there separately. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upynk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pynk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/01 6:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes...</span><hr size=1> Maybe a spell with a Knockback effect to interrupt casting with a 5 second Silence to prevent casting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mookus>Mookus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/01 9:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Use Invert Gravity to interupt casting. It works and it's quite amusing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvalenstormbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valen Stormbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 11:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Wizards already have this type of spell. Any of the magic based spells with a knock back effect will stop a gaint form casting Gate or Complete Heal.<br>
<br>
On a Kael runs I use Draught of Jiva to stop the different cleric type gaints form casting spells. If your not level 55+, try using the level 53 spell Jyll's Static Pulse (2.0 casting time will help stop any spell).<br>
<br>
Neither spell will stun a gaint but, it will interrupt their casting. Which is the goal anywaysl. Of course with the high resist of most of the velious mobs adding a lure type spell to this line would help alot. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvalenstormbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valen Stormbringer</A> at: 5/13/01 9:51:41 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=366.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=366.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=366.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=366.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=366.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=366.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2